title: chapter3_musing1
---
//Let the player walk around to pick up fruit
    //There are some fruit laid out neatly in front of the Pilgrim NPCs
    //There are also some fruit scattered and laid out throughout the level
WASD: Throughout the groves, I can see that Pilgrims have gathered. Ones who look to be from the Clan of old and others who look new to these lands.
WASD: These Pilgrims have come to lay out ritual fruit to match those Offered by the First Beings.
WASD: In this role, this Dedicant feels the responsibility placed upon her from both Clans. And the immense weight this union brings.
WASD: Once again, I am reminded that with time comes the loss of meaning. ...Which, admittedly, saddens me.
WASD: Although, it <i>is</i> promising seeing how ritual has grown into ceremony. Especially one so celebrated by many.
<<jump chapter3_musing2>>
===
title: chapter3_musing2
---
//While the player is still collecting fruit
WASD: This Dedicant has inherited the ideas of both Clans, now merged.
WASD: She has been brought into a multi-societal world; widened by new customs, lifestyles, and traditions.  
WASD: I can feel the pride she carries in spearheading the acceptance of the new Pilgrims.
WASD: This makes me eager to see how the grove will flourish and if it means the best of both will culminate.
<<jump chapter3_tree>>
