WASD: As the Dedicant collected the Pilgrims' fruit, a number of them remarked on how special the eclipse ceremony had become; most likely due to the rarity of its occurrence.   
WASD: Hear these comments, I began thinking...
WASD: Despite how auspicious my feelings have grown in this time, something began to nag within me.
WASD: For I fear that this ceremony gives way to spectacle. And I am unsure what that holds for the future.
